# CODEOWNERS — review ownership by path. GitHub auto-requests review from the
# owner(s) of the changed paths on every PR.
#
# To ENFORCE it (block merge until a code owner approves), turn on
# "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection / a ruleset for `main`.
# Note: on a solo repo this would block you (you cannot code-owner-approve your
# own PR) — enforcement is meant for team projects.
#
# Template notes:
#   - The owner handles below are the upstream template owner; `scripts/personalize.sh`
#     rewrites them to your GitHub owner on derive.
#   - If your owner is an ORGANISATION, replace handles with `@org/team`
#     (a bare `@org` is NOT a valid code owner), and split the zones below
#     across your real teams.

# Default — anything not matched by a more specific rule below.
*                       @VadayI

